- VSCode Version: 1.6.0
- OS Version: Windows 10

Steps to Reproduce:
1. This happens while working with [css-modules](https://github.com/css-modules/css-modules).
2. Write this css:

``` css
.error {
  /* csslint ignore:start */
  composes: content from "./Modal/Modal.module.css";
  /* csslint ignore:end */
  border-color: #DE3A3A;
  box-shadow: 0 0 20px -2px #DE3A3A;
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
}
```
1. vscode should not lint those lines. Ref: https://github.com/CSSLint/csslint/wiki/Ignoring-parts-of-CSS-during-linting

I have below keybinding configuration (to restore the old `cmd+e`) and it use to open a file when I release press/release `cmd+e` in the quick view. This stopped working (today?) and I have to press `enter` to open a file

```
    {
        "key": "cmd+e",
        "command": "workbench.action.quickOpen"
    },
    {
        "key": "cmd+e",
        "command": "workbench.action.quickOpenNavigateNext",
        "when": "inQuickOpen"
    }
```

